      "content": "it feels like the \"mainstream\" view you mentioned is basically just saying it's a net good, while the other stuff is treated like a edge case or a minor concern. isn't it kinda a stretch to call it a \"significant disagreement\" if the majority of experts agree it helps the economy overall?",
